# gen272, Italian mirror of teachverb.chat through the SAME code path: a fresh
# verb ("registra ") is deaf, is taught via the Italian label of the same
# learnable/3 row family ("verbo di insegnamento"), then teaches a greeting.
# One mechanism, two languages — the bilingual ratchet of LOOP.md.
> registra "ciao ciao" per salutare
< I don't understand that yet.
> insegna "registra " come verbo di insegnamento
< Got it - I'll take "registra " as a way to verbo di insegnamento now.
> registra "eccoti {name}" per salutare
< Got it - I'll take "eccoti {name}" as a way to salutare now.
> im anna
< Nice to meet you, anna!
> im bea
< eccoti bea